@@TJvComboListBox.HotTrackCombo
Summary
  Specifies whether a combo box is highlighted when the mouse passes over it.
Description
  Set HotTrackCombo to true to provide visual feedback about which combo box is under the mouse When
  HotTrackCombo is false, there is no visual feedback when the mouse passes over items of the list
  box.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvComboListBox.DropdownMenu
Summary
  Determines the pop-up menu to display when the user clicks the combo box button.
Description
  Assign a TPopupMenu to the DropdownMenu to display it when the user clicks the combo box button in
  the list box. DropdownMenu is separate from PopupMenu but can point to the same TPopupMenu if
  necessary.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TControl.PopupMenu>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvComboListBox.DrawStyle
Summary
  Determines how images are drawn in the list box.
Description
  Use DrawStyle to specify how images are drawn in the list box.
See Also
  TJvComboListBoxDrawStyle

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvComboListBox.Delete
Summary
  Deletes an item from the Items list.
Description
  Delete is equivalent to Items.Delete but also makes sure that if the item deleted contains a
  TPicture, the picture is freed.
Parameters
  Index - \Index of the item to delete.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TCustomListBox.Items>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvComboListBox.ButtonWidth
Summary
  Defines the width of the combo box button.
Description
  Use ButtonWidth to set the width of the combo box button in the list. The default width is 26
  pixels.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvComboListBox.AddText
Summary
  Adds a string to the list box.
Description
  Use AddText to add a string to the Items list. AddText is a helper function and is equivalent to
  calling Items.Add.
Parameters
  S - The string to add.
Return value
  Returns the index of the item in the Items list.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TCustomListBox.Items>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvComboListBox.AddImage
Summary
  Adds an image to the list box.
Description
  Use AddImage to add a TPicture to the Items list. AddImage is a helper function that assures that
  the image is copied to an internal TPicture and added to the Items.Objects list. You can also call
  Items.AddObject directly if you prefer.
Parameters
  P - The picture to add. A copy is created internally and added to the Items.Objects list.
Return value
  Returns the index of the item in the Items list.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TCustomListBox.Items>

